Vexa captures audio from Google Meet and Microsoft Teams meetings, transcribes it in real-time using Whisper AI, and provides a beautiful web interface to manage everything. Own your data, self-host everything, no cloud dependencies.

This template includes:
- Vexa API: The transcription engine with bot management
- Vexa Dashboard: Web interface for managing meetings and transcripts
- PostgreSQL: Database for storing all your data

Perfect for teams who want enterprise-grade meeting transcription without sending data to third parties.', 'transcription', ARRAY['Transcription', 'Meetings', 'AI', 'Productivity', 'Self-Hosted'], 'latest', NULL, ARRAY['ubuntu-22.04', 'ubuntu-24.04', 'debian-12'], ARRAY['docker', 'postgres'], $JSON${"image": {"type": "string", "title": "Image Docker", "default": ""}, "port": {"type": "integer", "title": "Port HTTP", "default": 3000}, "version": {"type": "string", "title": "Version", "default": "latest"}}$JSON$::jsonb, $JSON${"metadata": {"name": "Vexa Dashboard", "version": "latest", "description": "Vexa Dashboard is a complete, all-in-one solution for self-hosted meeting transcription. This template deploys both the Vexa API (real-time meeting transcription engine) and its web dashboard in a single click.\n\nVexa captures audio from Google Meet and Microsoft Teams meetings, transcribes it in real-time using Whisper AI, and provides a beautiful web interface to manage everything. Own your data, self-host everything, no cloud dependencies.\n\nThis template includes:\n- Vexa API: The transcription engine with bot management\n- Vexa Dashboard: Web interface for managing meetings and transcripts\n- PostgreSQL: Database for storing all your data\n\nPerfect for teams who want enterprise-grade meeting transcription without sending data to third parties.", "category": "transcription", "tags": ["Transcription", "Meetings", "AI", "Productivity", "Self-Hosted"], "os_support": ["ubuntu-22.04", "ubuntu-24.04", "debian-12"], "dependencies": ["docker", "postgres"]}, "params": {"image": {"type": "string", "title": "Image Docker", "default": ""}, "port": {"type": "integer", "title": "Port HTTP", "default": 3000}, "version": {"type": "string", "title": "Version", "default": "latest"}}, "links": [{"label": "Website", "url": "https://vexa.ai"}, {"label": "Documentation", "url": "https://github.com/Vexa-ai/vexa"}, {"label": "Dashboard GitHub", "url": "https://github.com/Vexa-ai/vexa-dashboard"}, {"label": "API GitHub", "url": "https://github.com/Vexa-ai/vexa"}], "instructions": "After deployment, open the Vexa Dashboard URL in your browser. You can immediately start joining meetings and transcribing them.\n\nTo enable AI-powered transcript analysis, edit the vexa-dashboard service environment variables and uncomment the AI_MODEL and AI_API_KEY lines.\n\nFor better transcription quality (requires GPU), edit the vexa-api service and change WHISPER_MODEL_SIZE from \"tiny\" to \"medium\" or \"large-v3\", and set DEVICE to \"gpu\".\n", "install": [{"docker": {"image": "$IMAGE", "name": "vexa-dashboard", "port": "$PORT:3000", "volumes": [], "extra_ports": []}}], "verify": [{"http_get": {"url": "http://localhost:$PORT", "expect": [200, 301, 302]}}], "output": {"url": "http://{{ server_ip }}:$PORT", "type": "webapp", "notes": "After deployment, open the Vexa Dashboard URL in your browser. You can immediately start joining meetings and transcribing them.\n\nTo enable AI-powered transcript analysis, edit the vexa-dashboard service environment variables and uncomment the AI_MODEL and AI_API_KEY lines.\n\nFor better transcription quality (requires GPU), edit the vexa-api service and change WHISPER_MODEL_SIZE from \"tiny\" to \"medium\" or \"large-v3\", and set DEVICE to \"gpu\".\n"}, "services": {"postgres": {"type": "postgres", "version": "latest"}}}$JSON$::jsonb, NOW()) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
